	}

	public static void main(String[] args){

	}
}

METHODS:
1. Build in: .substring(int beginningIndex)
2. User defined:
	a. return type - return primitive and non primitive values
	b. void - no value is returned

METHODS:
1. with parameters
2. without parameters
-----------------------
Java Modifiers:
1. Access modifiers: public, protected, default, private
2. Non access modifiers: static, final, abstract

public - access to all classes in the entire world (project)
protected  - access to all classes in the same package
default - access to all classes in same package
private - access within same class ONLY

SYNTAX FOR METHODS:

   OPTIONAL			OPTIONAL	   MUST			MUST	OPTIONAL
accessModifier nonAccessModifier returnType methodName (parameterList){
	 methodBody;
}

SYNTAX FOR VARIABLES:

  OPTIONAL			OPTIONAL      MUST    MUST
accessModifier nonAccessModifier dataType name;